The stations particularly affected by Toyota and bakkie-loving thieves include Hatfield, Centurion, Marlboro and Rosebank.Daan du Preez, who drives a Toyota Fortuner, said he had been parking in the "special bays" at Hatfield station for months.Gautrain spokesman Kesagee Nayager said cordoned-off parking had been created for high-risk vehicles.She declined to elaborate on additional security measures."With the assistance of the police we have identified high-risk vehicles like Toyota Hilux bakkies, among others, that are susceptible to theft, and have made special security provisions."-Additional reporting Graeme Hosken